More precisely, if \ab{ùë®}~\aof{‚àà}~\ab{ùí¶} and \ab h~\as{:}~\af{hom}~(\T{X})~\ab{ùë®}, then \ab h factors as \T{X} $\overset{\text{\ab h}}{\twoheadrightarrow}$ \af{HomIm}~\ab h $\overset{‚äÜ}{‚Ü£}$ \ab{ùë®} and \T{X}~\af{/}~\af{ker}~\ab h ‚âÖ \af{HomIm}~\ab h ‚â§ \ab{ùë®}; that is, \T{X}~\af{/}~\af{ker}~\ab h is (isomorphic to) an algebra in \af{S}~\ab{ùí¶}. Letting
\afld{‚âà} := ‚ãÇ \{\ab{Œ∏}~\aof{‚àà}~\ab{Con}~\T{X}~‚à£~\T{X}~\af{/}~\ab{Œ∏}~\aof{‚àà}~\af{S} \ab{ùí¶}\},
